An Air Force study of veterans who sprayed Agent Orange during the Vietnam War found the strongest evidence to date that exposure to the herbicide is associated with diabetes.
The feeling is that Agent Orange has caused many more health problems than the DOD and the VA have acknowledged in the past.
Defoliants -- including Agent Orange with its highly toxic component dioxin -- were sprayed over central and southern Vietnam during the war to eliminate cover for the Viet Cong and North Vietnamese army.
